    <h1>Slow Cooker Buffalo Chicken Lettuce Wraps</h1>
    <img src="https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/4RMG583ham7UsUA2TL-1dX7nhRA=/750x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():format(webp)/2240640_Slow-Cooker-Buffalo-Chicken-Lettuce-Wraps_Photo-by-Christina-1-9d05c1c81e2b4dcc8c4b74f051793c76.jpg"
    alt="Buffalo Chicken Lettuce Wraps">
    <h2>Discription:</h2>
    <p>Chicken breasts are topped with hot pepper sauce and dry ranch dressing mix and cooked in<br> 
        the slow cooker. When it's ready, just shred it up and fill fresh Boston lettuce cups. AC <br>
        says, "Quick, easy, and healthier than traditional Buffalo wings!Perfect for family dinners,<br>
        BBQ parties, football Sundays, or just about any event!"</p>
    <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>2 pounds skinless, boneless chicken breasts</li>
        <li>1 (12 ounce) bottle cayenne pepper sauce (such as Frank's® RedHot®)</li> 
        <li>1 (1 ounce) package ranch dressing mix</li> 
        <li> 1 head Boston lettuce leaves</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Steps</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Put chicken into the crock of a slow cooker.</li>
        <li>Stir cayenne pepper sauce and ranch dressing mix together in a bowl until smooth; pour<br>
            over chicken.</li>
        <li>Cook on Low for 6 to 7 hours.</li>
        <li>Transfer chicken to a large bowl and use 2 forks to shred chicken into strands.</li>
        <li>Strain liquid from slow cooker crock into a bowl to serve on the side.</li>
        <li>Spoon chicken into lettuce leaves and roll lettuce around chicken.</li>
    </ol>
</body>
